s:1128:"<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size:0.9375rem;"><strong>Course Completion Requirements: Geometry Fundamentals</strong></span><br /></p><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">To complete the Geometry Fundamentals course, you need to:</p><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr"></p><ol><li><strong>Complete All Modules: </strong>Successfully finish each module, covering key topics such as geometric shapes, theorems, properties of angles, and spatial reasoning.</li><li><strong>Pass Quizzes and Assessments:</strong> Achieve a passing score on all quizzes and assessments to demonstrate your understanding of geometric concepts.</li><li><strong>Participate in Practice Exercises:</strong> Engage in all practice exercises to apply and reinforce your geometric skills.</li><li><strong>Achieve a Minimum Grade:</strong> Attain the minimum grade set to ensure a thorough understanding of geometry fundamentals.</li></ol><p dir="ltr"><br /></p><p dir="ltr">Upon meeting these requirements, you will have demonstrated a strong grasp of geometric principles, preparing you for more advanced studies and practical applications in geometry.</p>";